			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The shadowknight is known as Paladin of Evil. For that, you may never be able to stand with NPC Paladin and Cleric.KoS(kill on Sight).... lotta KoS.You will get used to it. avoid any npc that says scowls at you... or they will attack you..<BR>
Yes, you get lots of KoS.Then why should you play SK? There are some reasonable reasons.<BR>
First of all , you can have a pet and you are a fine warrior youself.However your pet is much weaker than you .You will have to tank to protect your pet but having a pet helps you a lot.<BR>
Second , you have harm touch while Paladins have LOH(Lay ON Hand).The damage of harm touch depends on your level.(If you are level 10,the harm touch will do around 100 damage to monsters that con green and blue and black. Yellow and red might resist your harm touch.)<BR>
<BR>
Last ,you may look cool. There aren't many shadowknight in EQ world.Lotta people shout &quot;level # mage looking for a group&quot;,&quot;level # druid looking for a group&quot;,&quot;level #ranger,wizard,monk looking for a group.&quot; and you will shout &quot;level # shadowknight looking for a group&quot;. It may look cool that you are different from the others.<BR>
Once again, beware of being KoSed.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
