	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Shadow Knights are regarded by many as the easiest (and possibly the only) combination able to solo effectively. This does not preclude grouping of course, but at least it gives you the option to take on enemies if there is no-one around to group with.<BR>
<BR>
You can play your SK two ways - as a Human/Dark Elf and concentrate more on the Necromancer side - or as a Troll/Ogre and concentrate more on the Warrior side. I would recommend playing as a Troll for various reasons.<BR>
<BR>
As a magic user you don't get any spells until level 9. The spells you get then, and even the spells you get at level 15, are not powerful and are merely additionally helpful rather than being hugely useful. Therefore it is important to be an effective warrior rather than a spell caster - at least until later levels anyway. <BR>
<BR>
Your pet will never be able to tank for you - it will never be good enough - so being able to stand in the thick of it and take damage, and enable your pet to get a few additional blows in, is the best way to go.<BR>
<BR>
Ogres will always be better at pure fighting than Trolls - however I would strongly recommend Trolls rather than Ogres for the simple reason of Regeneration. As a SK you don't get any kind of healing spell until at least level 22 - and that means (unless you are fortunate to constantly group with a shaman or, God forbid, a Cleric/Bard/Paladin) a lot of down time sitting waiting for your hp's to return. Trolls heal at least twice as fast and this means you will be up and ready for combat much earlier than Ogres, or any other Warrior type races, for that matter.<BR>
<BR>
TSK's are great fun, the exp point penalty for being one does not seem to be excessive - I got to level 16 in about 5 days of playing (total time, not in one sitting obviously) and this does not seem to be much longer than most other races although I would expect there are many out there who have done vastly better and would disagree with me. I died a lot, unfortunately - but don't let me put you off - you will die a lot whoever you are.<BR>
<BR>
Above all enjoy it - whatever race you chose. And Bash All Dat Yu Sie...
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
