				I have a comment to make and opinion and well would like to see what someone<BR>
else thinks.<BR>
I have run a paladin on everquest untill that of 9th lvl and then I began to<BR>
run its counter part anti paldain so to speak shadow knight. A little look<BR>
into what the paladin and shadow knight are, paldins are 1/4 cleric and 3/4<BR>
warrior and shadow knights are 1/4 necromancer and 3/4 warrior so to speak.<BR>
The problem I am having is that well paldins have a special ability to lay<BR>
hands which is a heal of hp which works everytime once a game day. Now its<BR>
evil brother gets what is called a death touch which is a special power to<BR>
do damage that goes up as does the lvl of the SK but in contrast this<BR>
special power is resistable, why? Well in my opinion this is a special power<BR>
and shouldn't be resistable just like his goodie to shoes brother the<BR>
paladins lay hands. Either that or maybe the paladins lay hands shout have a<BR>
chance of failure then?<BR>
Also the paladin gets heal spells and such as he should , but the SK does<BR>
not get his version of this which is lifetap which is steal life from target<BR>
and add to yours why is this?<BR>
I think this is just a little much having a class that is suppose to be<BR>
equal to another but just of an evil aspect but yet besides being condemed<BR>
by all and the hardships of be shuned by all NPC's or attacked by them you<BR>
cant even heal yourself and must sit around for 20 to 30 min to heal after<BR>
big battles.<BR>
I feel that if these 2 minor flaws in the character where to be corrected it<BR>
would make for a much more rounded game play. Send me any opinions on this<BR>
maybe convince me why it shouldnt be this way.<BR>

