				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have Played all the melle classes at least to level 8(the monk I have is level 8) And most over 10 I have a 20th level warrior, a 13th level Ranger and I deleted a 12th level paladin.. I Started an SK on friday evening and made Level 9 last night, (about 12 hours total playing time, I had to put a level on my Enchanter (13) in the mean time so I couldnt spend all the time on the SK.) The Monk is cool.. but ladies and gentlemen, If you want to play a mellee class, and can live with being evil, SK is the way. It completely spanks the other Melee classes AS IS. The Monk is the only one close. Harm Touch may be usable once a day, but has kept me alive MANY times. and a few times it didnt keep me alive, it at least let me burn down an opponent so I did nt lose as much. This may get worse as time goes on, and I will see.. But from the looks of it now, with the spells, pet and Harm.. it is a brutal combo. If you need to be good, Well, I suggest a monk. Paladins and Rangers get some nifty stuff, but nothing spectactular (except for maybe the  holy swords) and Warrior simply dont do enough damage to be effective. I dust mine off only for special occations as he is the highest level character in my arsenal. (he is also my smith..)   
