				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am a troll SK and here are my observations:<BR>
1. KOS is bad.  I even work hard on my factions within my roleplaying context to small effect.  I spent about 2 weeks in BlackBurrow killing over 1000 gnolls for Qeynos factions only to find out that Corrupt Qeynos Guards will still KOS me even though I am now aimibale with good guards, so I still cant go in city.<BR>
2. Trade skills: forget it.  Not a single oven, kiln, forge, etc. in Grobb and you get KOS in some places in Oggok and Neriak you have 3 zones that you have to walk in duck mode due to tiny inkie doorways - that is painful!<BR>
3.  Harm Touch - better at earlier levels, always useful.  Gets resisted by reds, which makes sense cuz so do wizards spells and physical damage - this keeps you from killing above your level and gaining exp beyond your means, which makes sense.<BR>
4. Pet - only to add damage and take that 2nd Sand Giant hit when you get ambushed meditating so you have time to run away and live!<BR>
5. Regeneration - awesome at early levels, always useful.  Combining Regen with Harm Touch makes the first few levels for a SK a joke because the HT will take over 20% of a mobs total HP and your regeneration as a percentage to total HP early on is incredible.  I watched myself regenerate over two full bubbles during the course of a battle at an early level, 40% more HP for a fight!<BR>
6. Faction with PCs is what makes this class my favorate!  With just a little bit of roleplaying you become a character in Human lands that is unforgettable and everyone remembers you and enjoys your company, I am always being asked to group with others yet the class is still able to support solo play effectively.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
