	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Dumdum's guide Part 2<BR>
<BR>
Just a note to Grilli, thanks, got sense heading up to 30 now. Once you get above 12 or 15 it seems to increase faster.<BR>
<BR>
1.  Practice taunt, it will save your party members lives, although this seems not to work if they are to far gone or running away.<BR>
<BR>
2. become familiar with what your spells do, your siphon strenght takes strenght from your victim and gives it to you (once). If you continue to cast the spell you will notice it says the the victim weakens. Hit them with disease, you will only do 5 points of non-melee damage but i have noticed the spell also prevents them from regenning hp.<BR>
<BR>
3. Using harm touch to kill a scarab, ok, but i would advise not doing that in an area that has multiple aggro mobs. Many times i was taking out a derv and that mummy or dry bone skeleton (DB) would start hitting me from behind. A group of three or four lev 12 to 17 trolls can take out that DB but your harm touch will save a party member. don't waste it, at higher levels.<BR>
<BR>
4. Don't pass up any decaying skeletons or normal skeletons, you will find that a supply of bone chips comes in handy for creating your pet.<BR>
<BR>
5. Your pet is not a tank, (haven't tried this at 15 yet) countinuosly hit taunt to keep it from getting killed. If you need to run for a zone your victim will focus on your pet, giving you a chance to run. This will not work if you get into a battle will multiple mobs, count on you pet biting the dust in 2 or 3 hits.<BR>
<BR>
6. ok, biggie here.... do not complete a quest where you get exp when grouped, Exp will be with party memebers, wait until you disband to complete quests.<BR>
<BR>
7. Stay out of human camps, do not forget you are a troll and KOS. HEH HEH, I tried to walk into a gypsy camp to check out the wares, died 2 times getting corpse back. Make a Corpse hot key so you can drag corpse while moving backwards, this will save you a lot of stopping to type /corpse when trying to get corpse out of an aggro area.<BR>
<BR>
8. Im trying to get my beg skill up, be careful NPC merchants will attack you. Found that out the hard way too. Beg seems to work better on npc's that don't con red. I actually went up 1 point. Have yet to get anything from begging.<BR>
<BR>
9.  Level 15 now, and guess what, I finally resisted my first rabies spell. now have endure cold, and that let me resist some frost rift spells. have not noticed if damage is less at this point. more on this later.<BR>
<BR>
10. South Ro Desert, you will want to avoid these mobs unless in a group 4 or more, and even then someone will probably die: Crypt mummies, Dry bones Skeletons, Casting Dervs, Casting madmen, Terrorantula, Named NPC's.<BR>
<BR>
11. If you take these mobs on in a group, co-ordinate your attack, let the tank take the hits, if you have no healer in the group this is where taunt will save his life. If you take on groups of mobs ALWAYS take out the caster first. There is nothing like being hit for 1 -10 points and watching your hp bar slide over half way because all of a sudden you get hit by spells that take 20-30 hp a pop.<BR>
<BR>
Hope this helps some, more when i hit level 20<BR>
<BR>
Dumdum (Veeshan)
